Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto
a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into
thin strips.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use
a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the pepper to the frying pan and stir-fry until just soft,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Reduce the heat to medium, then add the garlic and @chipotle paste{20%g}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder). Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{} combine the @soured cream{50.25%g} and lime
zest. Set aside.

When the fajita mix is ready, add a generous squeeze of lime juice. Stir to
combine and remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, share the wedges between your plates and top with the
chicken fajita mix.

Sprinkle over the cheese. Finish with a dollop of the zesty soured cream -
wedges loaded!

Serve with any remaining lime cut into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!